value.title: Kamala Harris lands in Singapore for Asia visit that will include Vietnam stop
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris landed in Singapore on Sunday as she begins a visit to Southeast Asia that will also include a stop in Vietnam.

value.excerpt: West Virginia Attorney General Patrick Morrisey is suing the Biden administration over a key immigration policy reversal he says has fueled a "devastating" flow in the deadly drug fentanyl.

value.title: Republicans torch White House for claiming Biden never 'shies away' from questions
value.excerpt: GOP lawmakers are smashing Biden over White House communications director Kate Bedingfield’s Friday claim that the president does not turn away from questions.

value.excerpt: Former acting Director of National Intelligence Ric Grenell slammed President Biden for having "ignored the conditions" set by former President Donald Trump in his 2020 agreement with the Taliban.

value.excerpt: The White House doubled down on Kamala Harris' East Asia trip amid the Afghanistan crisis. An official said the United States "has many interests around the world."

value.title: UK member of Parliament: 'Shameful' for Biden to claim Afghan troops ran
value.excerpt: United Kingdom Member of Parliament Tom Tugendhat lamented the rise of the Taliban in Afghanistan while chastising President Biden for how he has blamed Afghan forces by accusing them of giving up.

value.excerpt: Vivek Ramaswamy, author of Woke, Inc., called out Vice President Kamala Harris for her silence as some Afghan women face civil rights violations at the hands of the Taliban. Ramaswamy called it a ‘wasted opportunity’ for the vice president who could have positioned herself as a leader on women's rights.

value.title: Pelosi, top House Dems won't budge in infrastructure tussle with moderates, tout Biden support for her 'rule'
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and her leadership team are mounting a pressure campaign on centrist Democrats to get them to support their party's budget resolution without a vote on the bipartisan infrastructure bill.

value.title: Vivek Ramaswamy blasts Twitter's 'staggering' hypocrisy on Taliban and Trump
value.excerpt: Biotech CEO and ‘Woke Inc.’ author Vivek Ramaswamy criticized Twitter on Tuesday for allowing the Taliban to utilize their social media platform while censoring others, including former President Donald Trump.

value.excerpt: A former assistant defense secretary warned that al Qaeda “will again show its viper head” and said President Biden was “disingenuous” and during his address Monday.

value.title: Biden approves Florida emergency declaration due to Tropical Storm Fred
value.excerpt: Biden ordered federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local response efforts -- because of emergency conditions resulting from the storm, according to a statement from the White House.

value.title: Trump calls on Biden to 'resign in disgrace' over crisis in Afghanistan
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump Sunday called on President Biden to “resign in disgrace” over his handling of the Afghanistan withdrawal and other issues.

value.title: Todd wondered if the messy Afghan withdrawal will 'weaken Trump's hold' of the GOP over time
value.excerpt: NBC anchor Chuck Todd spoke with certainty that the turmoil that has erupted during President Biden's military withdrawal in Afghanistan would have also occurred under President Trump.

value.title: Trump ally in Georgia running for lieutenant governor vows to 'expose all voter fraud'
value.excerpt: A state senator in Georgia who’s a strong supporter of former President Trump is vowing to "investigate and expose all voter fraud" as he runs next year for lieutenant governor.

value.title: President Biden, VP Harris avoid the cameras as Kabul falls to Taliban
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris have avoided going on camera as Kabul, the capital city of Afghanistan, fell to the Taliban on Sunday.

value.title: Newsom ramps up attacks in CA recall, slams Elder as further right than Trump
value.excerpt: Gov. Gavin Newsom ramped up his campaign to hold onto the governorship, slamming Republican opponent Larry Elder as more right-wing than former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Trump fundraises off ‘total loser’ Andrew Cuomo resigning
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump is fundraising off the resignation of “total loser” and soon-to-be-former New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo.

value.title: GOP demands Biden administration act after Mayorkas calls border crisis 'unsustainable'
value.excerpt: Top Republicans on Friday called on the Biden administration to act on the crisis at the southern border after leaked audio emerged of Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas calling the situation there "unsustainable."

value.title: Hannity: Biden's 'America Last' agenda putting more than just the US at risk
value.excerpt: In his Opening Monologue, “Hannity” host Sean Hannity challenged his audience to name a single positive accomplishment of President Joe Biden or his administration.

value.title: Biden backs Newsom as California recall election looms, urges residents to 'vote no'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden delivered his strongest endorsement to date for embattled Democratic Gov. Gavin Newsom on Thursday, urging Californians to reject an effort to recall the governor in an upcoming special election.

value.title: Biden adviser Anita Dunn leaves the White House

value.title: Biden EPA nominee touted ‘defund the police’ on Chinese state TV

value.title: Biden’s approval rating sinks to new low of 50% amid economic fears, polls show
value.excerpt: Support for President Joe Biden is taking a hit with his average approval rating sinking to a record low of 50 percent, new polls show.

value.title: Lara Trump torches Kamala Harris' 'spectacular' failures as VP on 'Fox & Friends'
